SUMMARY:Weekly Forest Park Tuesday Hike and Pizza (Lower Macleay to Pittock Mansion)
DESCRIPTION:Portland\, Outdoors (20s and 30s Hiking Group)\nA weekly hike up to Pittock Mansion to view the city!\n\nMiles: 5.0\nElevation Gain: 921 ft\n\nThings to bring: headlamp/flashlight during the short days of winter (it gets dark on this hike starting in September!)\, hiking boots\, water.\n\nPlease note that although this hike is relatively short\, the elevation gain in such a short period can be challenging for those that are beginning to hike. The group maintains a steady\, constant pace on the trail and if you cannot keep up\, keep hiking and we will wait at the top for you!\n\nThis hike is in the heavy woods of Forest Park and gets darker much earlier that the surrounding areas due to this tree coverage. We hike all year round and will shorten the hike during very rainy days in the winter to a 2.5-mile round trip hike.\n\nAlltrails link: Lower Macleay Park to Pittock Mansion on AllTrails\nhttps://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/oregon/lower-macleay-park-to-pittock-mansion?p=-1&sh=duboim
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/portland-outdoors-20s-and-30s-hiking-group/events/313258409/
