DTSTAMP:20260322T022053Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260502T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260502T160000
SUMMARY:Overnight Camp Trip and Hike: Badger Creek Trail
DESCRIPTION:Portland\, Outdoors (20s and 30s Hiking Group)\nCome join us for the first season's camp trip! We'll be camping on the east side of Mt. Hood in BLM land\, which allows for free\, dispersed camping on Friday night\, then hiking on Saturday morning. Please feel free to join us for one\, or both events! If you are interested in camping\, please comment or send me a message\, and I'll coordinate all of the campers together.\n\nHike Distance: 12 Miles\nHike Elevation: 1400 Ft.\n\nAlltrails link: [Badger Creek Trail\, Oregon - 197 Reviews\, Map | AllTrails](https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/oregon/badger-creek-trail)
